entry.tran: 强调成分(置于形容词、副词之前加强意义的词)
entry.def: In grammar, an intensifier is a word such as 'very' or 'extremely' which you can put in front of an adjective or adverb in order to make its meaning stronger.

means.word_mean: 1. a modifier that has little meaning except to intensify the meaning it modifies;

sentences.sentence: "`honestly' in `I honestly don't know' is an intensifier"
